import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='source', binwidth=10, color='blue', alpha=0.5, label='Source')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='target', binwidth=10, color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Target')
    plt.axvline(data['source'].mean(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Source')
    plt.axvline(data['target'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Target')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of module dependencies?')
    plt.xlabel('Module ID')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

data = pd.read_json('flare-dependencies.json')

top_10 = data.groupby('source').count().sort_values(by='target', ascending=False).head(10)

sns.set_style("whitegrid")
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(11.7,8.27)})
sns.barplot(x=top_10.index, y='target', data=top_10, palette='Blues_d')
plt.axhline(y=top_10['target'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {top_10['target'].max():.2f}")
plt.legend()
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.xlabel('Module ID')
plt.ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
plt.title('Which module has the highest number of dependencies?')
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

data = pd.read_json('flare-dependencies.json')

sns.set(style="whitegrid")
sns.boxplot(x=data['source'], y=data['target'], color='skyblue')
plt.title('What is the average number of dependencies per module?', wrap=True)
plt.xlabel('Source Module ID')
plt.ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
plt.axhline(y=data['target'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    no_dependencies = data['target'].value_counts().loc[lambda x: x==1].count()
    has_dependencies = data['target'].value_counts().loc[lambda x: x>1].count()
    sns.barplot(x=['No Dependencies', 'Has Dependencies'], y=[no_dependencies, has_dependencies])
    plt.title('Are there any modules that have no dependencies?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Number of Modules')
    plt.xlabel('')
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
